document_data.History:
[[File:Palace of Passion 2.png|thumb|''Embracing lovers on the Lovers' Walk.''|370x370px]]
The original Palace of Passion was destroyed in a fierce battle between the [[avatar]] of Sune and [[Baatezu]] [[Glasya]], the lord of [[Malbolge]] and daughter of [[Asmodeus]]. The heroic battle brought hordes of new worshipers to the goddess of beauty, and a mere year later, the temple was rebuilt through generous donations from rich artists, merchants, nobles, and social climbers.{{Cite polyhedron/136/City Stories: The Temple of Selûne|10}}

On the [[Mirtul 10|10{{th}} of Mirtul]], the same year as the temple's destruction, the Palace of Passion, aided by temples of Lliira, Sheela Peryroyl, and Hanali Celanil, hosted the first [[Annual Beautification Day]], a festival dedicated to improving one's looks. The first attempt did not reach desired popularity. However, the newly rebuilt temple had grand plans for the following celebration.

document_data.Inhabitants:
*[[Aesthetia]], the cleric who ran the temple's infirmary in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite polyhedron/144/The Palace of Passion: Ravens Bluff's Temple of Sune|44}}
*[[Angela Sunshine]], a younger priestess in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Candi Kane]], a young cleric in charge of the Body Beautiful program in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Carlotta de Amourette]], a [[Knights of the Golden Rooster|Knight of the Golden Rooster]] and a stunning Dame of Raven's Bluff who was in charge of the trample's festivals and celebrations in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite polyhedron/144/The Palace of Passion: Ravens Bluff's Temple of Sune|43}}
*[[Corwell Fanfare]], once a High Priest of Ravens Bluff, a traveling preacher and cleric of the goddess who reportedly visited his deity in [[Arborea]] in the late 14{{th}} century DR.{{Cite polyhedron/144/The Palace of Passion: Ravens Bluff's Temple of Sune|45}}
*[[Gregor Fenfrill]], a tall powerful and gorgeous man in charge of clergy recruitment in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Ilbrar the Iron]], husband of High Priestess Morlain and the administrative supervisor of the temple in the late 14{{th}} century DR.
*[[Morlain]], the High Priestess of the Palace of Passion in the late 14{{th}} century DR who had time to start homeless aid programs and teach beautification classes.
*[[Perilily]], less attractive and less intelligent than many of her fellow clergy members, Perilily was a temple greeter and the infirmary healer in the late 14{{th}} century DR.

Other junior clergy members included [[Clarice]], [[Amber (Ravens Bluff)|Amber]], [[Ruby (Ravens Bluff)|Ruby]], [[Tisane]], [[Dirk (Ravens Bluff)|Dirk]] and [[Steel (Ravens Bluff)|Steel]].
